INSERT INTO public.procurement_line_years (line_id, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, appr_code, ba, line_number, title, quantity, unit_cost, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$PROC_NAVY_NA_L0017$$, 2027, $$Navy$$, $$PROC_NAVY$$, $$NAVY$$, NULL, $$17$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$ set may not be exact or sum exactly due to rounding.

 Justification:
 The FY 2027 request supports the procurement of three Low Rate Initial Production (LRIP) MQ-25 aircraft, and the advance procurement of long-lead materials in support of five in LRIP (Lot 3) MQ-25 aircraft.
 The LRIP contract award is planned for March 2027 and the LRIP Advanced Procurement contract award is planned for January 2027. Additionally, FY2027 will see an increase in funding requirements for
 obsolescence, the procurement of Airframe Peculiar Ground Support Equipment (PGSE) and Peculiar Training Equipment.

 Engines and Contractor Furnished Equipment (CFE)/Government Furnished Equipment (GFE) cost elements are to procure specific equipment needed for that year's aircraft buy. GFE includes, but is not limited
 to, Advanced Networking Tactical System (ANTS), Multifunctional Information Distribution System (MIDS)/Joint Tactical Radio System- (JTRS), Conformal-Controlled Reception Pattern Antenna (C-CRPA),
 Advanced Digital Antenna Production -Antenna Electronic (ADAP-AE), Wideband SATCOM terminals and Commercial SATCOM service (Skyhook), Electro-Optical/Infrared (EO/IR), Air Refueling Pod (ARS A/
 A42R-1), and Airborne Radio Communications (ARC-210).

 REC Flyaway ECO is required to address design changes and design corrections in order to incorporate these into the production line.

 NRE supports the activities required to forward fit the LRIP with baseline changes from obsolescence or identified during SDTA+ Flight Test and Production Configuration Audit.

 Obsolescence supports life-of-type (LOT) procurements for ~30 components across 8-10 subsystems identified as obsolete or at risk of end-of-life (EOL). These components are required for LRIP Lot 2 and must
 be procured early to avoid redesign, cost growth, and schedule delays.

 Airframe PGSE is required to establish and maintain intermediate level maintenance capability at operational sites and aboard Aircraft Carriers, Nuclear (CVN), and depot level maintenance capability standup
 at the designated source of repair facilities for depot operations, and at operational sites. Includes costs for supplier technical data development and delivery, technical publication development, training, support
 equipment, tools, and other supporting logistics elements. Funding ensures critical capability is in place to support reduction of repair turnaround time and 90 day unreplenished requirements in support of the
 MQ-25's Mission Capable Aircraft Readiness (MCAR) and Fully Mission Capable Aircraft Readiness (FMCAR) goals.

 Peculiar Training Equip includes funding for Mission System Trainer (MST) located at Pt. Mugu, CA, which includes costs for Fleet Replacement Squadron (FRS), NAWCAD Simulation Division (SimDiv), and
 additional hardware. Funding also supports AVP Contract Instructors (CIs), Weapons Systems Trainer (WST), Part Task Trainer (PTT), Deck Operator Trainer (DOT), and courseware.

 Production Support requirements are for Government and Contractor Support Services (CSS) annualized support of the overarching production program. Production Support requirements are annualized efforts
 required to provide acquisition support, aircraft configuration management, supportability standup activities, and engineering support for production.

 Integrated Logistics Support requirements are for the portion originally embedded in "Production Support" that organically provides logistics elements for stand-up activities associated with aircraft production and
 eventual fleet transition.

 Publications Tech Data supports the costs required to forward fit the initial LRIP technical publications with baseline changes from obsolescence or identified during SDTA+ Flight Test and Production
 Configuration Audit. This includes the development and distribution of maintenance repair manuals essential for operation and sustainment of production aircraft.


