 Justification:
 The Marine Corps requires five additional MUX MALE MQ 9A aircraft to meet updated operational demand. Current inventory no longer meets sustained Reconnaissance, Surveillance, Target Acquisition (RSTA)
 and maritime domain awareness requirements identified in revised force employment projections. Additional aircraft provide required capacity and resilience for Marine Expeditionary Force (MEF) level littoral
 sensing and data distribution in support of competition, deterrence, and conflict operations.




