 Justification:
 The overall goal of the modifications budgeted in FY2027 is to implement commonality/capability and structural safety and reliability improvements. OSIPs 11-10, 11-13, 14-03, & 20-14 can be found in LI-0525
 for FY20 and prior. FY21 and out resides in LI-0505.

 OSIP 11-10 EA-18G Unique funding enables four Growler Capability Modification (GCM) lines to meet the Navy's Master Aviation Plan capacity in support of COCOM capability requirements. This OSIP supports
 the required safety-of-flight modifications, mitigation of obsolescence issues, and incorporation of system improvements.

 OSIP 11-13 Power and Propulsion incorporates safety and life-limiting propulsion and power corrective actions to resolve safety and readiness concerns. Corrections to design deficiencies found during post-
 production test and evaluation, and discovered during fleet operations, that have resulted in safety and reliability degradation, must be corrected. Implementation of Air Turbine Starter kit improvement to resolve
 potential non-containment incidents, as well as ECP5069 FADEC cooling line and generator cable chafing improvement to mitigate risk of fuel leaks. To address reliability degradation, implementation of Data
 Reduction Program (DRP) is in work to enable data collection on test cells specifically for the F414 engine. The requirement to upgrade or modify the engine and its support systems, data systems, secondary
 power system, electrical system, and fuel systems is critical in maintaining sustainable fleet reliability, safety, tooling, and performance and is necessary to meet mission requirements. FY2027 funds Generator
 Converter Unit (GCU) Feeder Wire modifications that are required to support the aircraft power growth for service life extension.



