 Justification:
 This budget request supports the MQ-9A with the integration of capability (payload/sensors) modifications and modernization.

 FY 2027 funds the procurement of Detect and Avoid System (DAAS), Electronic Warfare (EW)/ Cloud Surfer II High, Airborne Network Extension (ANE) / SkyTower II, DuraNET, Centerline Avionics Bay (CAB),
 Proliferated Low Earth Orbit (PLEO), Identification Friend or Foe (IFF), Radar Electronics Assembly (REA), Automatic Identification System (AIS) and NRE in support of payloads, data, training equipment,
 support and associated installs. Additionally, the MQ-9A system will continue to evolve and upgrade its capabilities to address reliability, maintainability, correction of deficiencies and safety issues as they arise.
 Funding may be used to address Diminishing Manufacturing Sources (DMS) issues. The required upgrades include, but are not limited to, aircraft, sensors, ground control stations, ground support system retrofit
 to baseline configurations, the Common Computing Environment (CCE) architecture and spares for modified components.




