 Description:
 This OSIP incorporates changes to H-1 avionics systems, specifically addressing and enabling the Marine Corps top three priorities (Lethality, Digital Interoperability (DI), and Survivability). Additionally, this
 OSIP attacks the highest readiness degraders to reduce the total cost of ownership while improving Mission Capable Aircraft Requirement (MCAR) and Full Mission Capable Aircraft Requirement (FMCAR)
 rates. Improvements to safety of flight, maintenance, obsolescence (Diminishing Manufacturing Sources/Material Shortages), and readiness degrader items will yield a more interoperable and survivable H-1
 force to sustain warfighter capability in support of worldwide operations. Systems modified and improved on H-1 aircraft will leverage common architectures and utilize existing technology to the maximum extent
 practical to minimize development and procurement costs and to reduce the time to field the modifications. Funds will be used for ancillary support such as mission planning, conditioned based material planning/
 execution, and software support requirements.

 FY2027 funds utilization:

 -DI Link-16 effort: FY2027 continues procurement of 24 A/B Kits, Training Equipment, and Installations which will allow H-1 aircraft to operate with digital interoperability throughout training and contested
 environments. Link-16 aligns with the Marine Corps priority of Digital Interoperability by providing Maritime Multi-Domain awareness/Kill-web enabler and effector, facilitates command and control, H-1 air-to-air/
 air-to-ground shore based and maritime information sharing, shortens the kill chain, and improves battlefield information and intelligence sharing. Digital Interoperability and access to joint tactical data links is
 essential for the current and future operating environment. By 2029, H-1s will be one of just two aviation fires platforms in Marine Corps Aviation with the sundown of F/A-18. Timing of this investment is critical
 to ensure schedule for OSIP 12-24 and the ability to field advanced weapons such as the Precision Attack Strike Munition (PASM), a 200nm+ weapon system. Digital Interoperability Link-16 requires enabling
 technology to include the Advanced Data Transfer System (ADTS) and WiFi filter.

 -Terrain Awareness Warning System (TAWS) II: FY27 will continue the procurement of 75 B-Kit updates to the Aircraft Wiring and Integration Remote Terminal (AWIRT) to provide new aural alert in support
 of Terrain Awareness Warning System (TAWS) II. TAWS II provides H-1 a significant safety improvement in Controlled Flight Into Terrain (CFIT) protection by providing a forward-looking, terrain-predictive
 protection against terrain and man-made obstacles.

 - Install Equipment N/R: FY27 begins the non-recurring Cryptographic Modernization (CM) effort for the H-1's avionic cryptographic systems in accordance with National Security Agency (NSA) mandates,
 transitioning them to a post-quantum resistant state.

 - Training: FY2027 continues procurement of DI-Link 16Flight Trainer Devices (FTD) and starts procurement of Composite Maintenance Trainer (CMT) modifications.



