 Description:
 This Operational Safety Improvement Program (OSIP) is necessary to support Navy T-6 airframe and propulsion system modifications required to mitigate safety, reliability, obsolescence, DMSMS and user
 capability gaps. Funding provides for the nonrecurring engineering (NRE), ECP processing, kit procurement and retrofit of the aircraft airframe, power plant, propeller and associated GBTS and Support
 Equipment systems. Funded efforts in this OSIP include but are not limited to Rudder Pedal Shaft replacement, ECP 6038J - Under Water Activated Release System (UWARS), T-6B Emergency Locator
 Transmitter (ELT) replacement, 0106A Concentrator Improvement and other airframe system changes driven by obsolescence and DMSMS issues.

 DEVELOPMENT STATUS/MAJOR DEVELOPMENT MILESTONES: Continuation of modification program funding to meet evolving mission training requirements and mitigate emergent issues related to safety,
 aircraft age, obsolescence and supportability factors that diminish Navy pilot training program aircraft and GBTS readiness.




