INSERT INTO public.procurement_line_years (line_id, fiscal_year, service, appropriation, appr_code, ba, line_number, title, quantity, unit_cost, prior_year_actual, current_year_enacted, request_amount, fydp_yr1, fydp_yr2, fydp_yr3, fydp_yr4, narrative, content_hash, source_pdf, source_page, ingested_at) VALUES ($$PROC_NAVY_NA_L0045$$, 2027, $$Navy$$, $$PROC_NAVY$$, $$NAVY$$, NULL, $$45$$, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, $$ set may not be exact or sum exactly due to rounding.

Justification:
FY 2027 request procures GAU-21 and M240D machine guns, in addition to funding all associated support costs of the Common Defensive Weapon System (CDWS) efforts associated with Engineering
Change Proposals (ECP's) to the weapon system. This includes updates to technical data packages (TDPs), Kit parts procurement and fielding, provisioning and sustainment requirements in direct support of
modifications to the weapon systems.

FY 2027 funds additional Future Readiness Team initiative to procure and field newly designed Aircraft Interface Units (AIU's) from the Small Business Innovative Research (SBIR) effort for the Linkless
Ammunition Loading System (LALS) III system. This affects the sustainment program for the LALS III, improve Mean Time Between Failure (MTBF) and reduce the number of LALS III failures, thereby increasing
LALS III availability. This would also decrease maintenance man-hours being expended repairing the LALS III system.

FY 2027 funds support transition of the GAU-17 7.62 machine gun to the GAU-24 7.62 machine gun on the UH-1Y helicopter. The GAU-24 transition is required to address pending obsolescence issues with the
GAU-17. This transition ensures continued UH-1Y combat effectiveness while improving reliability, maintainability, and life-cycle cost as well as resolving lack of contracting capability.




