 Description:
 DESCRIPTION/JUSTIFICATION: The Common Defensive Weapon System (CDWS) consists of a GAU-21 .50 caliber Machine Gun, M240D, GAU-17 & GAU-24 7.62 Machine guns, cradles, ammo boxes, feed/
 link chutes, lasers and platform specific mount system for US Navy and Marine Corps assault and assault support helicopter platforms to include the MV-22, CH-53E/K, UH-1Y, and the MH-60 R/S. This budget
 procures and replaces the one for one weapon as it is determined to be beyond repair, to the fleet forces. CDWS was established to replace the obsolete GAU-16 and XM-218 .50 caliber Machine Guns. CDWS
 enhances the warfighters overall capability by providing a safer, more reliable and accurate weapon systems with a higher rate of fire. Additionally, this budget is used to accomplish NRE and production related
 tasks related to system obsolescence in support of GAU-17 and LALS III.




