 Justification:
 FY 2027 request supports the procurement and installation of aircraft and ground segment retrofit kits. OSIP 009-18 funding request supports one (1) aircraft retrofit kit procurement and the installation of one (1)
 aircraft retrofit kit.

 Additionally, the FY 2027 request supports the remaining OSIPs and continues to address: (1) Aircraft Platform Systems Correction of Production Deficiencies and Modernization, (2) Ground Segment
 Improvements and Modernization, and (3) Payloads Mission System Improvements and Technology Insertion.

 The overall net decrease in funding levels from FY2026 to FY2027 is due to the completion of upgrades to ground segments that ensure configuration alignment with aircraft modifications. Future planned ground
 segment modifications incorporate critical systems and software changes.

 ECPs address safety, reliability, maintainability, suitability degradation in aircraft systems and capability improvements that will be incorporated via government led biannual software releases. Furthermore,
 ECPs support modernization requirements for avionics and airframe components via DMSMS and engineering changes. Effort includes the correction of supportability and interoperability deficiencies, resolution
 of aircraft systems obsolescence, and weight savings initiatives through insertion of commercial and government off the shelf (COTS/GOTS) technology onto the MQ-4C.



