Justification:
AUTOMATIC TEST EQUIPMENT:
FY 2027 provides funding to offload multiple weapon system Operation Test Program Sets (OTPSs) to CASS, RTCASS, eCASS, and the Joint Services Electronic Combat Systems Tester (JSECST) from
various legacy systems to include, Signal Generator Test Set (SGTS) an Electronic Warfare (EW) O-Level test system. Funding also for production of several High Speed Subsystem (HSS) ancillary assets.

A/C COMMON SUPPORT EQUIPMENT:
FY 2027 provides funding to procure CRAFT Replacement, Next Generation Software Loader Upgrade, Mobile Nitrogen Gas Generator, Particle Counters, AECTS Replacement/Modification, Engine Test
Instrumentation Replacement System (ETIRS), First Destination Transportation Cost for hardware, TPS Migration, Engineering Change Proposals to address minor CSE performance and obsolescence issues
as well as associated support cost.

ICP/HEADQUARTERS MANAGED SUPPORT EQUIPMENT:
FY 2027 provides funding for the procurement of end items of out of production weapon systems and Common Support Equipment (CSE) Deficits/Replacements under the budget, procurement and inventory
control of Naval Inventory Control Point (NAVICP).

PECULIAR SUPPORT EQUIPMENT:
FY 2027 provides funding to procure PSE for the V-22, E-2C/D, F/A-18A-F/EA-18G and various out-of-production aircraft to fill Fleet site inventory deficits along with replacing PSE that has parts obsolescence
issues and no longer cost effective to use.

CONSOLIDATED AUTOMATED SUPPORT SYSTEM:
FY 2027 provides funding to procure (5) eCASS Mid-Life UPGRADE (MLU), (12) Fourth-Generation Electro-Optics (EO4) and associated ancillary equipment.

MOBILE MAINTENANCE FACILITIES:
FY 2027 provides funding to procure (40) MFs and associated support costs.


