 Description:
 This Other Procurement, Navy line item supports the Golden Fleet Strategy by rapidly fielding many resilient, aeratable systems with diverse capabilities such as the key programs within the Unmanned Surface
 Vehicle (USV) Family of Systems (FoS). The sUSV Portfolio consists of a family of systems designed to meet an urgent Geographic Combatant Command Requirement. The sUSV FoS fulfill's the Navy's
 emergent need to operate sUSVs with autonomous software while operating at long distances. The Navy defined the emergent need to operate and refine tactics with the sUSVs through two efforts. A single
 sUSV within the sUSV FoS consists of a USV, a communications system, a command and control (C2) station, the procurement and integration of autonomy software, and a payload that will be integrated once
 the USV is delivered.

 The GARC is an unmanned vehicle that requires a high bandwidth datalink to operate at long distances. Additionally, the platform is equipped with a radar, infrared devices, and capable of carrying various
 payloads. The platform includes an autonomy ready package, high-definition surveillance cameras, and remote command and control capabilities. The CORSAIR program consists of a combination of sUSVs
 that will be used to conduct Naval operations to meet an urgent Geographic Combatant Command Requirement. sUSV CORSAIR is a production-ready, inexpensive Maritime capability leveraging the best of
 commercial technology and innovations at speed and scale.

 The One Way Attack (OWA) Surface program consists of sUSVs that will be used to conduct Naval operations to meet an urgent Geographic Combatant Command Requirement. Which is a production-ready,
 low-cost Maritime capability leveraging the best of commercial and government technology and innovations at speed and scale.

 Starting in FY2026, LI 0956 has been established for Small Unmanned Surface Vehicles. The Small Unmanned Surface Vehicle Family of Systems was previously funded under LI 1210 H00014.

 The FY2026 spend plan for 0956 Small Unmanned Surface Vehicles (sUSV) includes $0 million of discretionary and $1,406 million of mandatory for a total of $1,406 million.




