 Description:
 NOTE: Effective FY 2026, all funding and programs within OPN Budget Line Item (BLI) 2176 moved into OPN BLI 2136 in support of the Program Element (PE)/BLI consolidation initiative prescribed within the
 'DoD Implementation Plan from the Commission on Planning, Programming, Budgeting and Execution (PPBE) Reform Final Report', to facilitate the effort to rapidly increase Navy Lethality in the Submarine and
 Surface Fleet.

 This Budget Line Item (BLI) consists of three separate and distinct programs, the OPNAV N98 sponsored Aircraft Carrier Tactical Support Center (CV-TSC) program, the OPNAV N96 sponsored Sonar Dome
 Rubber Windows (SDRW) program, and the OPNAV N2N6 sponsored Undersea Warfare Decision Support System (USW-DSS) program.

 Program Descriptions:

 AIRCRAFT CARRIER TACTICAL SUPPORT CENTER (CV-TSC) (Cost Code VM301):
 The AN/SQQ-34 Aircraft Carrier Tactical Support Center (CV-TSC) program delivers Anti-Submarine Warfare (ASW) and Surface Warfare (SUW) combat capability to the Aircraft Carrier supporting Aircraft
 Carrier, Nuclear power (CVN) Tactical Action Office (TAO) and embarked Carrier Strike Group (CSG) Sea Combat Commander. The program provides validation and certification of Engineering Changes (ECs)
 fielded on CVNs and provides hardware/software changes/upgrades to previously fielded and in-production CV-TSC systems required to correct deficiencies identified through Fleet use, upgrade unreliable/
 unsupportable components, replace obsolete components, and resolve Information Assurance (IA) issues. The program maintains interoperability with current and future interfaces to stay within the current
 performance envelope, supports mission data exchange, improves ASW/SUW track/sensor processing and analysis techniques, improves mission planning, improves data recording, reconstruction, and
 distribution, improves embedded simulation and training capabilities and implements cyber-security measures to effectively employ overall CVN Self Ship Defense System (SSDS) capabilities. CV-TSC integrates
 sensor data from organic Aircraft (MH-60R), organic platform sensors and tracks via Ship Self Defense System Product Line Architecture (PLA) and non-PLA, Link-16 track data, Global Command and Control
 System (GCCS) Over-the-Horizon track data, and Environmental and Threat Databases to assess the threat and assist the Tactical Action Officer and Carrier Strike Group to effectively employ overall CVN self-
 defense capabilities. CV-TSC generates real-time ASW/SUW information and recommendations, tactical planning and employment of ASW/SUW assets, ASW/SUW sensor data processing and analysis, and
 distribution of tactically significant data. Aircraft supported include: MH-60R/S Seahawk, P-8 Poseidon, MQ-4C Triton, and future ASW/SUW non-organic supporting platforms.

 SONAR DOME RUBBER WINDOWS (SDRWs) (Cost Code VM401):
 AN/SQS-53 Sonar Dome Rubber Windows (SDRWs) are installed on all CG47 and DDG51 class ships (Initial Capabilities Document (ICD) for ASW, AN/SQQ-89(V) Operational Requirements Document (ORD)
 (#667-76-05 dated August 2005). This program provides emergency replacement, wire-reinforced, pressurized rubber acoustic windows and attachment hardware, which experience failure due to corrosion,


