 Description:
 The Submarine Acoustic Warfare System (SAWS) program provides submarines with expendable defensive countermeasures and the systems necessary to launch them against torpedo and acoustic sensor
 threats. This program provides ongoing production of countermeasure devices needed to sustain fleet inventories, improvements to enhance the readiness and effectiveness of countermeasure devices and
 associated External Countermeasure Launcher (ECL) systems on all U.S. submarines. Acoustic Device Countermeasures (ADC) are expendable devices produced in two primary versions. The Internal
 Countermeasure Launcher (ICL) launches the 3" ADCs and ECL Systems launch the 6" devices.

 WM014 6 Inch Countermeasures: Funding under this cost code procures and supports 6" Countermeasures, ADC MK3 (torpedo), and ADC MK4 (SONAR) countermeasures for submarine protection. The effort
 includes unit costs of the new devices, reworks, and the system engineering, which covers the associated support costs at the Technical Design Agent (TDA) and In-Service Engineering Activity (ISEA). For every
 procurement of 6-inch ADC, supplementary MK77 shall be procured.

 WM015 3 Inch Countermeasures: Funding under this cost code procures and supports 3" Countermeasures ADC MK2 for submarine protection. This effort includes the unit costs of the devices as well as the
 system engineering services, which covers the associated support costs at the TDA and ISEA. The effort also includes procurement of an enhanced ADC MK2 MOD 8/9 that provides the Fleet with greater
 functionality.

 WM018 Acoustic Augmentation Support Program (AASP): Funding under this cost code provides acoustic augmentation systems in appropriate configurations for all submarine classes (except SEAWOLF). The
 equipment is installed as temporary equipment Temporary Alteration (TEMPALT) until Ship Alterations (SHIPALTs) can be permanently installed to reduce sustainment costs and provide a long-term solution. A
 combination of new procurement systems and refurbished systems are required to complete installations. Reliability and refurbishment upgrades provide current in-service AASP systems with new components
 and software updates to maintain reliability. AASP new procurements are required a year prior to installation and refurbished systems are required the same year as installation.

 WM019 Countermeasure Set, Acoustic (CSA) Program: Funding under this cost code procures and supports the inboard electronic system necessary for preparing and launching 6" ADCs from all 688i and
 newer U.S. submarines. This inboard system consists of the Torpedo Defense Controller (TDC), Launch Control Panels (LCPs), and associated cabling, in a class-by-class configuration. The CSA program
 continually modernizes and technical refreshes system hardware and software. Five efforts are supported: (1) The "CSA SWFTS Integration" effort is maintaining the integration of the CSA system with the
 SWFTS System of Systems (SoS). Implementation of a phased approach allowed incremental implementation of capabilities. Required funding addresses recurring upgrades within the SWFTS Technology
 Insertion (TI)/Advanced Processor Build (APB) cycles to maintain compatibility with networked tactical systems and continue to reduce cybersecurity risks. (2) The ongoing "CSA MK4 Technology Insertion"
 effort replaces the CSA MK2 MOD2 with a SubTDS-capable, SWFTS-integrated CSA MK4 system on VIRGINIA Class Block I and II submarines (10 hulls). (3) The "CSA SEAWOLF SWFTS Integration" effort


