 Description:
 The Naval Tactical Command Support System (NTCSS) is the logistics information system which enables combat lethality by generating and sustaining Navy and Marine Corps force maintenance and logistics
 readiness for operational commanders afloat and ashore. NTCSS provides organizational maintenance management capabilities for all afloat and ashore operational forces (ships, submarines, expeditionary,
 and cyber), as well as organizational and intermediate maintenance management to maintain operational availability of deployed and deployable aircraft. NTCSS also provides personnel administration
 capabilities, planning and execution of warehouse and inventory management functions for repair parts and consumable material, financial accountability thereof, and support services of food and afloat retail
 point-of-sale operations. NTCSS system upgrades procures afloat and ashore ruggedized, commercial-off-the-shelf (COTS) computing equipment, which includes servers to support the NTCSS application and
 database, personal computers (PCs) that will interface with the servers for maintenance and supply transactions, and printers to display output. COTS software, which includes the operating system, comes
 loaded on the servers and PCs.

 The Naval Operational Business Logistics Enterprise (NOBLE) family of systems includes Naval Operational Supply System (NOSS), and Naval Maintenance, Repair, and Overhaul (N-MRO), and Logistics
 Integrated Data Environment (L-IDE). The NOBLE family of systems will provide direct support to warfighter readiness with maintenance, supply, and personnel administration capabilities using an open
 architecture framework that incorporates business process re-engineering (BPR) allowing for the consolidation of standalone application systems. These capabilities include enterprise-wide automation of supply,
 inventory, and financial functions to the Naval supply system, aviation maintenance support capability that services aviation maintenance (organizational and intermediate) for over 2,100 Navy and Marine Corps
 aircraft, standardized operational business processes for afloat maritime maintenance activities to all naval ships, expeditionary forces and Navy-wide personnel and administration data sharing across shipboard
 and shore-based information systems. NOBLE will meet current and emerging demands for cyber, Financial Improvement and Audit Readiness (FIAR), and Navy logistics and aviation and maritime maintenance
 mission requirements.

 Naval Operational Supply System (NOSS) will deliver a solution with enterprise and field level capability to ensure effective and efficient supply operations. NOSS will enable the planning, procurement and
 physical/financial accountability of all material and property across all warfare communities.

 Naval Maintenance, Repair, and Overhaul (NMRO) combines the former Naval Aviation Maintenance System (NAMS), Naval Operational Maintenance Environment (NOME) capabilities into one program of
 record (PoR) that satisfies Organizational and Intermediate levels of maintenance across ashore and afloat Aviation and Maritime domains.

 Logistics Integrated Data Environment (LIDE) is the DON Logistics and Sustainment information domain enterprise data environment which support DON Chief Information Officer (CIO) data strategy,
 architecture, and integration with DoW and DON level enterprise data environments.


