 Description:
 Magnetic Silencing Facility Upgrades support hardware, auxiliary systems, and support in association with the upgrade of current aging or new installation of CONUS and Outside Continental United States
 (OCONUS) Magnetic Silencing Facilities in order for the calibration of new Open-Loop Magnetic Systems or Advanced Degaussing System ships and submarines to be accomplished for worldwide operation.
 Upgrades obsolete high-power equipment to provide the necessary magnetic field for ensuring current and future navy ships and submarines meet requirements for Electromagnetic Signature Requirements and
 reduces susceptibility to Electro-Magnetic threat systems.




